Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.77,0:01:34.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.74,0:01:37.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,On that stormy day that announced\nthe end of spring,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.81,0:01:41.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...my friend and I arrived in Paris,\nwhere the boy awaited us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.01,0:01:47.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I tremble in silence at these\nemotions which leak out...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.35,0:01:50.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...as the hour of reunion\ndraws near.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.89,0:01:57.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This must be\nyour guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.01,0:02:19.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, if you don't mind, I'd like you to join us\nfor dinner after you've met my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.29,0:02:28.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.26,0:02:33.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it is not\ntoo much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:39.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please do. After all, we owe you\nour son's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.10,0:02:42.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to our home,\Nmy good Count of Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:54.06,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 4:\NA Mother's Secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.79,0:03:01.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To our new friend, the\NCount of Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.60,0:03:08.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:11.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm embarrassed that you\Nknow of the Janina campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:15.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The people praise me\nas a hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.04,0:03:18.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but to a soldier, such\nthings mean little.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:21.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,After all, nothing good ever\nresults from destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.91,0:03:26.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, these idyllic times in which we live\nwere built on the back of sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:28.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Such is my opinion,\nat any rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:30.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that the far corners\nof the galaxy are echoing...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.09,0:03:33.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...with the name of\NGeneral Morcerf by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.72,0:03:35.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You honor me\nby saying so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.54,0:03:54.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear, the food wasn't\nto your liking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.71,0:03:58.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. Please, think\nnothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.25,0:04:03.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am in the habit\nof eating very little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.62,0:04:07.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say that I don't\nunderstand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.66,0:04:12.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Having advanced in years, I find myself\Nweary of extravagant meals such as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.40,0:04:16.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In my case, I find lately\nthat I seldom sleep, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.17,0:04:20.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm amazed that you've managed\nto stay healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:23.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is because\nof these.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:26.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are they some sort\nof space rations?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:29.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the course of wandering the\nsea of stars for so long,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.78,0:04:33.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...my body and soul have changed\nbeyond recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:37.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I hope that you\Nwould at least eat something...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.35,0:04:41.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The thought of neither sleeping\nnor eating is too sad to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.59,0:04:42.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Too sad to bear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.02,0:04:44.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.03,0:04:49.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, perhaps\NI shall sample this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.57,0:04:52.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.81,0:05:07.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This taste brings\nback memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:09.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Brings back memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.48,0:05:13.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I once experienced delightful cooking\nsuch as this in the south of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.26,0:05:18.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the dish that you've made for as\nlong as I can remember, right, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.33,0:05:20.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:23.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,By any chance, you wouldn't happen\nto be from Marseilles, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:24.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.03,0:05:28.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My wife has nothing to do\Nwith such a barbaric province.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:30.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right,\NMercedes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:32.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:34.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.78,0:05:36.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.15,0:05:39.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One of my friends\nis from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.88,0:05:43.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Maximilien Morrel.\NHe's a really nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.79,0:05:45.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Morrel...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:50.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me if I misspoke.\NPlease, do not take offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.29,0:05:53.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.06,0:05:58.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our family traces its roots back\nto a powerful Catalan family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:02.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This soup has been a specialty of my\Nwife's ever since she was a young girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.47,0:06:06.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see. So, you and the Countess\nwere childhood friends, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.41,0:06:07.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.68,0:06:11.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Which explains why you seem so close.\NI am jealous beyond words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.65,0:06:17.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea that a man like you could\nbe jealous of anyone, Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.35,0:06:18.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.99,0:06:21.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If that person is a man\nof your father's caliber.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.42,0:06:26.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get the Count something to drink.\NHis glass is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.50,0:06:37.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please stay for as long\nas time permits.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:41.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sitting around the table like this, it almost\nfeels as if you are a member of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.75,0:06:54.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a maddening scent\nthis is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:56.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.66,0:06:58.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is from the\nmuscat grapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.29,0:07:01.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fatigued?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.66,0:07:08.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, please forgive me for\nforcing you to eat earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.70,0:07:12.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. I had always hoped to\Nexperience that delicious flavor again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:15.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was a sublime\nexperience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.98,0:07:17.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was a simple\nrustic dish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.81,0:07:20.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it makes me happy\nto hear you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.35,0:07:27.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard of this?\NThere is a saying that goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.99,0:07:32.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Those who share bread and salt under\nthe same roof become eternal friends."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.83,0:07:36.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is a tradition handed down\Nin Eastern Space, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.40,0:07:37.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.43,0:07:42.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that we are now friends.\NFor all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.94,0:07:47.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, this is not Eastern Space.\NIt is Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.28,0:07:53.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In Paris, everlasting friendship is impossible\nwithout the act of sharing bread and salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.75,0:07:59.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your soup truly\nwas delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.25,0:08:02.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Warm, and yet evocative\nof past memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.66,0:08:05.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is something\nwhich gives comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.39,0:08:08.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like a breeze blowing across\nthe Mediterranean Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.73,0:08:12.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count, are you very familiar\nwith Marseilles?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:15.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I could say that\NI am aware of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:21.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But perhaps I never truly\nknew it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.94,0:08:26.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Infidelity. Adultery.\NDalliances in the dead of night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.68,0:08:30.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You aristocrats are as energetic\nas the rumors say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.62,0:08:32.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me your\ncrude comments!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.55,0:08:34.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count is a friend\nof mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:36.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, you're such\na child.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.73,0:08:40.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If people could become friends simply\nby sharing bread and salt,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.53,0:08:41.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...life would be simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:43.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you\ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:46.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You'll understand sooner\nor later, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.68,0:08:58.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am most grateful to you for allowing me\nto experience a day such as today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.08,0:09:04.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. I'm proud that I had the\Nopportunity to introduce you to my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.12,0:09:06.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To introduce a\nman I admire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.26,0:09:09.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What say you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.32,0:09:13.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to invite you to my residence\non the Champs-Elysees in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.36,0:09:15.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:19.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count of Monte Cristo was a\Nmysterious man, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.93,0:09:24.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. There was a sternness somewhere\nin him that keeps people at arm's length.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.61,0:09:28.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That just means that compared to the Count,\nthe people of Paris are dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.71,0:09:29.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.11,0:09:33.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You might not know this, Mother, but\nthere's more to the world than Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.52,0:09:38.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Out beyond the walls, there's a world\nthat's endlessly captivating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.05,0:09:42.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think you've changed\nsince your journey to Luna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.19,0:09:45.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My journey is\njust beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:48.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go to worlds too far\nremoved from our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.93,0:09:52.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should exercise moderation\nin your association with the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.77,0:09:56.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please, Mother...\NYou sound just like Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:09:58.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, even though he seems\nmore than a little shady,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.97,0:10:01.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...having the Morcerf family establish ties with\na man like him might not be a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:05.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not when this family is about to\Nthrow its hat into the political arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:12.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief, why do aristocrats\Neat like this all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.15,0:10:14.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dinner parties, high tea,\nballs...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.52,0:10:17.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably because they\Ndon't have anything else to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.66,0:10:20.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, if you took away\nthe gluttony, lust, and avarice,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.86,0:10:22.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...there wouldn't be\nanything left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:24.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You need to watch\nyour mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.17,0:10:29.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you think that their guest today\nwas rather elegant and handsome?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.24,0:10:31.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so sure.\NHe wasn't very refined.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.64,0:10:36.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but he had a pretty good vibe going\nwith the mistress under the grapevine trellis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.48,0:10:41.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What, really? I'd always thought that the master\nwas the only man in the world for the mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.98,0:10:45.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think that any society lady would fall for\nthat Count if he worked his mojo on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:47.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a rest, already!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.06,0:10:52.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was definitely the face\nof a woman in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.36,0:10:55.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't stop that,\NI'm going to report you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.36,0:10:56.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oo, I'm so scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:01.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's preposterous. Mother is the last person\nin the world who would be capable of...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:11.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.52,0:11:20.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's in that picture\nshe's looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.66,0:11:30.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you find me\na horrible man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.90,0:11:33.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. I will stay at your side\nfor as long as I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.30,0:11:37.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that means walking down\nthe path to ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.04,0:11:41.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is not we\nwho will be ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.23,0:12:05.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have come home,\NFather.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.72,0:12:22.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What, you're still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.69,0:12:25.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't touch those!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.99,0:12:28.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to break it to you, but I've gotten\ninto your father's good graces,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.56,0:12:30.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so I'll be staying here\nfor a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.86,0:12:32.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His "good graces"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.56,0:12:35.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It means that your father\nis a man like any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.67,0:12:40.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Give those bad jokes\na rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.54,0:12:42.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, setting aside your\nfather for the moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.64,0:12:45.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the one that I'd be worried about\nis your mother, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.41,0:12:47.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed\nto mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.01,0:12:51.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, she was staring so wistfully\nat that picture of a young man...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.91,0:12:53.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You saw that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.02,0:12:56.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was definitely\na picture of a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.55,0:12:58.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A man who wasn't\nyour father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:02.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.52,0:13:05.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If my mother was staring at a\npicture of some strange man,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.23,0:13:06.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...l'd be depressed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.76,0:13:08.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's about enough!\NGet out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.13,0:13:09.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.18,0:13:25.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie? I didn't know\nyou were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.31,0:13:27.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ever the late riser,\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.42,0:13:29.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed\nlike that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.32,0:13:31.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong\nwith it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:33.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Skirts just don't work\non you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:36.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come here\nto see you, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:38.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then don't have me dragged\nout of bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.93,0:13:42.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who had you\nwoken up, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.37,0:13:49.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is something\nthe matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.07,0:13:50.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.97,0:13:53.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie is your fiancee,\nisn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.61,0:13:56.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's only natural that you\nshould greet her when she's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.88,0:14:00.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I suppose.\NUm, are you going somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.42,0:14:02.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we're just going out to do\na little shopping together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.98,0:14:04.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Madame!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.85,0:14:05.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.69,0:14:13.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me. What's this I hear about the\NCount of Monte Cristo inviting you over?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.56,0:14:14.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How did you\nknow that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.80,0:14:16.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it\nfrom Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.63,0:14:19.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He said that he and Maximilien\nwere also invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:21.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They were invited, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.25,0:14:38.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's he...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.72,0:14:41.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Peppo!\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.79,0:14:43.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hi, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.39,0:14:46.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you "Oh, hi!" me!\NDon't play around with Mother's jewelry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.39,0:14:48.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But they're so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.23,0:14:51.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If my father sees you like that,\Nthere'll be hell to pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.97,0:14:55.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, fine.\NI'll put them back, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.28,0:15:05.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're dying to know\Nwhat's in there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:10.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's like your mother's secret\Ntreasure is hidden inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.92,0:15:13.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.82,0:15:18.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's no such thing as a human being\nwho doesn't have secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:21.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just like you and I share\na certain secret night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.10,0:15:24.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That only happened because\NI was tricked by you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.90,0:15:28.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever want that lock opened,\ncome tell me anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.87,0:15:31.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I specialize in getting\ninto people's drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.77,0:15:33.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop being crude,\nand get back to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.24,0:15:35.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.03,0:15:52.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.36,0:15:56.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why would Mother have\na picture of the Count?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.84,0:16:07.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous.\NWhat am I so worried about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.89,0:16:27.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His Excellency General Morcerf!\NTen-hut!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.78,0:16:42.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All high and mighty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.18,0:16:52.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How do I look?\NNot too strange, I hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.79,0:16:54.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks wonderful\non you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.42,0:16:57.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.26,0:17:00.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.\NYou're more upbeat than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.06,0:17:01.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gee, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:07.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For a visit to the Count's place, that outfit isn't\nquite flamboyant enough, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.90,0:17:12.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not flamboyant enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.08,0:17:20.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert? What in the world\nare you wearing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.68,0:17:21.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong\nwith it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:23.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where do I\neven begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:25.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never understand the ways\nof you aristocrats.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.69,0:17:27.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed\nlike a pirate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.96,0:17:31.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, what are you even\ndoing here, Beauchamp?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.33,0:17:35.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't expect me to miss my chance to\nget photos of the Count's mansion, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.83,0:17:41.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, brother. And here I had hoped to go\nthere by myself, if at all possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.00,0:17:47.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That day when I first met you, you made me\nrealize that there is always hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.04,0:17:51.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...regardless of the circumstances\nyou might find yourself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:55.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I will never forget\nthat lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:17:59.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:05.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I was flung out of the Chateau d'lf\ninto the black void of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.76,0:18:12.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...hope was the one thing\nthat I had in my possession.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.88,0:18:25.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure\nthis is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.01,0:18:29.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. number thirty, Champs-Elysees.\NNo doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:32.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot more austere than I expected\nit to be, considering the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.55,0:18:37.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting the sort of place that would\ndrive a commoner into a rage if he saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:49.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, messieurs.\NWe have been expecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.61,0:18:54.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Early Rococo, huh?\NAnd not Revival, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.71,0:18:59.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.11,0:19:02.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's a bit too far removed\nfrom my world...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.95,0:19:08.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please pardon the delay.\NAllow me to show you to the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.12,0:19:10.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.86,0:19:12.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're going down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.39,0:19:15.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Baptistin, where are\nwe going?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.01,0:19:33.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:39.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, messieurs.\NThe Count awaits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.79,0:19:41.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.24,0:20:02.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even the floor and columns are gold...\NThe man has expensive tastes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.31,0:20:06.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where could he have gotten\nthis much gold?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.35,0:20:09.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I think there's\nsomething fishy about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:12.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, I bet his bed and\Npillows are gonna be solid gold, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.32,0:20:15.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never be able to fall asleep\nwith all this glare.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.29,0:20:16.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.03,0:20:20.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.93,0:20:21.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.90,0:20:23.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait.\NLook at that sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:27.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's artificial?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.84,0:20:29.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.97,0:20:32.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This alone would make\none hell of a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.58,0:20:41.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is so beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.08,0:20:44.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I know\nthis view!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.39,0:20:54.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That look suits you quite well,\nSir Pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.86,0:20:55.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.50,0:21:00.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:14.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind, I would like\Nyou to have this, Sir Pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.35,0:21:23.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was given this blade by a\ncertain ship's navigator.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.16,0:21:31.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it will serve to protect you,\nas well as to carve a path for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.76,0:23:12.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When we meet someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.17,0:23:15.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the selfless, considerate part of us\nclashes with the selfish love of our emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.34,0:23:18.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo, act 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:20.58,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 5:\NDo You Love Your Fiancee?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.81,0:23:20.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."Do You Love Your Fiancee?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.31,0:23:23.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
